children.text: There has not been a waterstop installed around the periphery of the insert bath/spa openings, and they’ve either been fitted off and connected to the waste in position.
The relevant Australian Standard AS 3740 Waterproofing of Domestic Wet Areas, requires in clause 3.8 Baths and Spas that
‘For insert baths, a water stop shall be installed around the periphery, see figure 3.2 (c)

This water stop should have been correctly installed in accordance with the requirements of AS 3740 Waterproofing of Domestic Wet Areas. I note that it is not practical to re-build the bath area to prevent the possibility of future damage, so it is recommended that a visual inspection of this area be conducted periodically to ensure the performance of the silicone joints, and re-apply as required.
